# Component Boundaries

- Keep each React component file under 300 lines.
- Prefer one primary concern per file (UI rendering, data fetching, state orchestration, utility helpers).
- If a component grows, split by concern:
  - move pure helpers to `*-utils.ts`
  - move async/network/state workflows to `use-*.ts` hooks
  - move large visual sections into focused subcomponents
- Keep prop interfaces and shared view-model types in nearby `types.ts` files when reused.
- Favor composition over deeply nested conditionals in a single component file.

# Practical Rule of Thumb

When adding a new feature to an existing component, check file length first. If it is near 250+ lines, extract the new behavior into a sibling hook, utility, or presentational child component.
